defintion:
base URI
internet media type for the data,e.g., JSON, XML, Atom, Images...
standard HTTP methods: GET, PUT, POST, DELETE
hypertext links to reference state
hypertext links to reference related resources

Collection URI
http://example.com/resources
GET: list URIs and other details of the collection members
PUT: replace teh collection with another collection
POST: Create a new entry in the collection. The new entry's URI is auto-assigned and ususally returned by the ops
DELETE: delete the entire collection

Element URI
http://example.com/resources/item17
GET: retrieve a rep of the addressed member of the collection in an Internet media type
PUT: replace the addressed member or create one if it doesnt exist
POST: Not generally used
DELETE: delete the addressed member of the collection

PUT and DELETE are idempotent
